  <notes>
    <completed-date>2025-12-30</completed-date>
    <implementation-summary>
      Extended existing AiTelemetry with comprehensive metrics for all AI operations.
      Enabled OpenTelemetry configuration in Program.cs for metrics and tracing export.

      Metrics Added:

      1. RAG Search Metrics (ai.rag.*):
         - ai.rag.requests - Total RAG search requests
         - ai.rag.duration - Total search duration (ms)
         - ai.rag.embedding_duration - Embedding generation duration (ms)
         - ai.rag.search_duration - Azure AI Search query duration (ms)
         - ai.rag.result_count - Number of results returned
         - Dimensions: ai.status, ai.cache_hit, ai.error_code

      2. Tool Execution Metrics (ai.tool.*):
         - ai.tool.requests - Total tool executions
         - ai.tool.duration - Tool execution duration (ms)
         - ai.tool.tokens - Token usage (input/output)
         - Dimensions: ai.tool_id, ai.status, ai.error_code, ai.token_type

      3. Export Metrics (ai.export.*):
         - ai.export.requests - Total export requests
         - ai.export.duration - Export duration (ms)
         - ai.export.file_size - Exported file size (bytes)
         - Dimensions: ai.format, ai.status, ai.error_code

      Files Modified:

      1. Telemetry/AiTelemetry.cs:
         - Added RAG, tool, and export metric counters and histograms
         - Added RecordRagSearch(), RecordToolExecution(), RecordExport() methods
         - Updated documentation with Application Insights query examples

      2. Services/Ai/RagService.cs:
         - Injected AiTelemetry (optional dependency)
         - Added telemetry recording on success and error paths

      3. Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs:
         - Injected AiTelemetry (optional dependency)
         - Added timing and telemetry for export operations
         - Records format, duration, file size, and error codes

      4. Program.cs:
         - Enabled OpenTelemetry configuration
         - Registered Sprk.Bff.Api.Ai and Sprk.Bff.Api.Cache meters
         - Configured distributed tracing with Sprk.Bff.Api.Ai source

      ADR-015 Compliance:
      - Only identifiers logged (analysisId, documentId)
      - No document content or PII in telemetry
      - Error codes without sensitive details
      - Correlation IDs via HttpContext.TraceIdentifier

      Application Insights Queries:
      - RAG P95: customMetrics | where name == "ai.rag.duration" | summarize percentile(value, 95)
      - Tool success: customMetrics | where name == "ai.tool.requests" | summarize count() by customDimensions["ai.status"]
      - Export by format: customMetrics | where name == "ai.export.requests" | summarize count() by customDimensions["ai.format"]

      Note: Tool execution telemetry injection into individual tool handlers
      was deferred - the RecordToolExecution method is ready but handlers use
      their own timing and the ToolResult already includes ToolExecutionMetadata.
    </implementation-summary>
